<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11105e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11105e">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11105e"> 105(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">C</font> forger</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A generation later, a priest of Asia Minor writes the Acts of PAUL, with the object of doing honour to the apostle. His authorship of the book is detected, <mark>his book is regarded as an imposture</mark>, and he is degraded from his office. So Tertullian tells us, placing the event in his own time. <small> James, M. R, ed., <a name="APOC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#APOC"><cite title="source">The Apocryphal New Testament</cite></a> (1924) xx</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
